Content:: Toto Landero (20 October 1995 – 4 July 2022)[1] was a Filipino professional boxer who challenged for the WBA minimumweight title in 2018. He died in 2022 after drowning in the Tabla River.[2] Landero has challenged for two minimumweight world titles in 2018; firstly the WBA title in March, where he lost to Knockout CP Freshmart by unanimous decision. Simphiwe Khonco then defeated Landero in July via the same result to retain his IBO title.
